Surface Steam compat-tools dir, filter PIDs by union, skip orphan kill, scrub env via cmd

Four GLF-OS-only changes bundled in this patch, each one needed
to make EA App / Origin / Battle.net launchers work end-to-end
from Lutris (EA App login + start + actually launch a game).

1. lutris/util/wine/proton.py: also yield the user's Steam
   compatibility-tools directory in `_iter_proton_locations()`.
   Vanilla Lutris only scans `settings.WINE_DIR` and Steam library
   `common/` subdirs; Proton dropped in by
   `programs.steam.extraCompatPackages`, our systemd-user
   `glf-proton-{ge,cachyos}-link`, or downloaded via Faugus is
   invisible to Lutris. Without this, EA App's yml requests
   UMU-Proton-10.0-4 but `is_proton_version()` returns False,
   `Wine.get_executable()` falls back to wine-ge (plain wine, no
   umu, no pressure-vessel), the umu-built prefix immediately
   crashes under bare wine, and EALauncher.exe dies in seconds.

2. lutris/runners/wine.py (filter_game_pids): switch from
   intersection to union for Proton paths.
   Once change (1) routes the launch through umu-run, the Proton
   branch returns `(folder_pids & uuid_pids) | gamescope_pids`.
   EA App spawns children with CreateProcess(...,
   inheritEnv=false, ...), so EADesktop / game wine64 hosts lose
   LUTRIS_GAME_UUID. The intersection collapses, beat() sees no
   tracked PIDs as soon as EALauncher.exe exits ~30 ms in. Union
   keeps a process counted as "ours" if EITHER its cmdline lives
   in the prefix container OR it carries the UUID.

3. lutris/game.py (beat): stop killing wine processes when
   game_thread dies but tracked PIDs still alive.
   Vanilla beat() has two on_game_quit branches: (a) game_thread
   dead AND game_pids empty; (b) game_thread dead AND game_pids
   non-empty -> `force_stop_game(pids)` (== wineserver -k). For
   launcher patterns, branch (b) is the killer: EALauncher dies
   ~30 ms in, change (2) means game_pids contains EADesktop &
   friends, Lutris winekills the entire prefix within 5 s of
   the user clicking Play. Turn (b) into a no-op: keep watching
   until game_pids legitimately reaches zero.

4. lutris/runners/wine.py (get_command): inject `env -u VAR ...`
   before the wine command to scrub Linux/desktop env vars EA
   App's serializer cannot handle.
   EA App's eax::foundation::serializeEnvironmentImpl caps the
   env block it can pass to a child game process at ~32 KiB. On
   NixOS the GNOME/KDE session env baseline is ~17 KiB and once
   umu-launcher injects pressure-vessel + Steam Runtime
   LD_LIBRARY_PATH/STEAM_COMPAT_*/WINEDLLOVERRIDES, the env
   crosses 40 KiB and EA logs "Cannot serialize environment:
   too long, NNNNN" + InvalidEnvironmentData on every game
   launch.

   We do this scrub *in the command list* (`env -u VAR1 -u
   VAR2 ... gamemoderun umu-run game.exe`) rather than in
   MonitoredCommand.get_child_environment. The previous attempt
   to scrub via get_child_environment broke the lutris-wrapper
   Python script that monitors children -- it lost critical env
   vars, exited within ~2 seconds without ever writing the
   /tmp/lutris-<UUID> status file, and Lutris saw "Game still
   running ... very short time, did it crash?" three times in a
   row when the user clicked Play. Pushing the scrub down to the
   command list keeps lutris-wrapper's env intact while still
   delivering a scrubbed env to the actual Wine subprocess via
   `env -u`.

Drop list mirrors the Faugus scrub
(pkgs/faugus-launcher/runner-protonfixes.patch):
  GNOME/GTK/Nix:    GI_TYPELIB_PATH, GTK_PATH, GIO_*,
                    GSETTINGS_SCHEMA_DIR, NIX_PROFILES, ...
  KDE/Plasma:       KDEDIRS, KDE_FULL_SESSION, KIO_*, ...
  XDG dirs:         XDG_DATA_DIRS, XDG_CONFIG_DIRS
                    (desktop-identifier vars KEPT, see below)
  Qt theming:       QT_PLUGIN_PATH, QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME, ...
  Cursors/docs:     XCURSOR_PATH, INFOPATH, MANPATH, ...
  Linux interpreters: PERLLIB, PERL5LIB, PYTHONPATH

KEPT: GST_PLUGIN_* (winegstreamer), XDG_*_HOME (Wine shader
cache), XDG_SESSION_TYPE (X11/Wayland), PATH, LD_LIBRARY_PATH,
LD_PRELOAD, HOME, USER, DISPLAY, WAYLAND_DISPLAY, XAUTHORITY,
XDG_RUNTIME_DIR, DBUS_SESSION_BUS_ADDRESS, WINE*/PROTON*/
STEAM*/UMU*/GAMEID/STORE, LANG/LC_*/TZ, PULSE_*/ALSA_*,
VK_ICD_FILENAMES/VK_LAYER_PATH, __NV_*/__GL_*/DXVK_*/VKD3D_*,
and the desktop-identifier vars XDG_CURRENT_DESKTOP /
XDG_SESSION_DESKTOP / XDG_SESSION_CLASS / DESKTOP_SESSION
(< 100 bytes total but Mutter / GNOME Shell / dash-to-dock
need them to drive the dock auto-hide on Wine fullscreen
windows -- without them the in-game window does not trigger
the _NET_WM_STATE_FULLSCREEN handshake and the dock stays
visible over the game).

The non-Proton wine fallback (`super().filter_game_pids(...)`)
is unchanged.
